doc.after: Professional wrestling or pro wrestling is a non competitive professional sport which is also considered an athletic performing art containing strong elements of catch wrestling mock combat and theatre It has origins in carnival sideshows in the late 19th century as part of displays of athletics and strength Modern professional wrestling usually features striking and grappling techniques which are modeled after diverse sets of wrestling and pugilistic styles from around the world
